  <bridgehead id='space'>Space around punctuation</bridgehead>

  <para>In most typographic traditions, some amount of white space
  appears around some punctuation signs. The &#x201C;Lexique des
  r&#x00E8;gles typographiques&#x201D; provides the following
  guidelines:</para>


  <informaltable>
    <tgroup cols='3'>
      <thead>
        <row>
          <entry>before</entry>
          <entry>punctuation sign</entry>
          <entry>after</entry>
        </row>
      </thead>

      <tbody>
	<row>
	  <entry>pas de blanc</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>,</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>pas de blanc</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>.</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>espace fine ins&#x00E9;cable</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>;</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>espace fine ins&#x00E9;cable</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>!</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>espace fine ins&#x00E9;cable</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>?</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>espace mots ins&#x00E9;cable</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>:</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>tiret</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>&#x00AB;</entry>
          <entry>espace mots ins&#x00E9;cable</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
          <entry>espace mots ins&#x00E9;cable</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>&#x00BB;</entry>
	  <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>(</entry>
	  <entry>pas de blanc</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>[</entry>
	  <entry>pas de blanc</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>pas de blanc</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>)</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>pas de blanc</entry>
	  <entry align='center'>]</entry>
          <entry>espace justifiante</entry>
	</row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>


  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>pas de blanc:</emphasis> no white space</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>espace justifiante:</emphasis> justifying space</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>espace fine ins&#x00E9;cable:</emphasis> non-breaking thin space</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>espace mots ins&#x00E9;cable:</emphasis> non-breaking word space</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>tiret:</emphasis> dash</para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
      

  <para>There are different approaches for the representation of those spaces:</para>

  <informaltable>
    <tgroup>
      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>espace justifiante</emphasis></entry>
          <entry>U+0020 SPACE</entry>
          <entry>U+0020 SPACE</entry>
          <entry morerows='2'>U+0020 SPACE</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>espace fine ins&#x00E9;cable</emphasis></entry>
          <entry>-</entry>
          <entry>U+202F NARROW NO-BREAK SPACE</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>espace mot ins&#x00E9;cable</emphasis></entry>
          <entry>-</entry>
          <entry>U+00A0 NO-BREAK SPACE</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>In this translation, we adopted the third approach. The text
  we provide can be transformed to the other approaches, by removing
  the U+0020 before &#x201C;:&#x201D;, or replacing it with
  U+202F.</para>

